===评价===
《我们的孩子，我们自己》获得了较为正面的评价，许多评论员都赞赏了米歇尔和卡梅隆故事主线的结局。电视小队的乔尔·凯勒（{{lang|en|Joel Keller}}）给出正面评价，表扬了其中“好笑的时刻”，但觉得还不够满足，希望可以得到更多的信息以便更清晰地了解所有的事情<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aoltv.com/2011/01/13/modern-family-season-2-episode-12-recap/ |title='Modern Family' Season 2, Episode 12 Recap |author=Keller, Joel |date=2011-01-13 |work=TV Squad |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110310033846/http://www.tvsquad.com/2011/01/13/modern-family-season-2-episode-12-recap |archivedate=2011-03-10 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。[[影音俱樂部|影音俱樂部]]的约翰·特蒂（{{lang|en|John Teti}}）称这一集的表现“不怎么样”，主要批评的是杰伊和格罗丽娅的桥段，他最终对节目的总体评分为C+<ref name="avclub">{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/our-children-ourselves,49865/ |title=Our Children, Ourselves |author=Teti, John |date=2011-01-12 |work=''The A.V. Club'' |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009213513/http://www.avclub.com/articles/our-children-ourselves%2C49865/ |archivedate=2012-10-09 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。《{{link-en|纽约 (杂志)|New York (magazine)|纽约}}》的雷切尔·马多克斯（{{lang|en|Rachael Maddux}}）称赞节目中让各个角色走出原本一本正经的生活环境与世界上的其他乡亲们进行互动<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2011/01/modern_family_recap_croctopus.html |title=Modern Family Recap: Croctopus |author=Maddux, Rachael |date=2011-01-13 |work=''New York'' |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511121808/http://www.vulture.com/2011/01/modern_family_recap_croctopus.html |archivedate=2013-05-11 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。[[電視指南_(美國雜誌)|电视指南]]的马特·罗什认为这一集的所有故事线索都“大获全胜”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Matts-TV-Week-1027683.aspx |title=Matt's TV Week in Review – Today's News: Our Take |publisher=''TV Guide'' |date=2008-10-01 |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019173843/http://www.tvguide.com/News/Matts-TV-Week-1027683.aspx |archivedate=2012-10-19 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。電視指南的乔伊斯·英格（{{lang|en|Joyce Eng}}）和凯特·斯坦霍普（{{lang|en|Kate Stanhope}}）之后总结认为米歇尔和卡梅隆的故事线索是2011年1月6日至13日这一星期最美妙的时段<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Moments-Modern-Family-1027665.aspx |title=Top Moments: Modern Family Comes Up Short, Top Chef's Avian Rap – Today's News: Our Take |publisher=TVGuide.com |date=2008-10-01 |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019173920/http://www.tvguide.com/News/Moments-Modern-Family-1027665.aspx |archivedate=2012-10-19 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的莱斯利·萨维奇（{{lang|en|Lesley Savage}}）认为这一集的表现不及《拖邻居后腿》，但米歇尔和卡梅隆的故事线索也“太他妈好笑了”<ref>{{cite web|last=Ward |first=Kate |url=http://tvrecaps.ew.com/recap/modern-family-season-2-episode-1/ |title=Modern Family recap: Shortcomings | Season 2 Episode 12 | EW.com |publisher=Tvrecaps.ew.com |date=2011-01-13 |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130130180712/http://tvrecaps.ew.com/recap/modern-family-season-2-episode-1/ |archivedate=2013-01-30 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。《[[時代_(雜誌)|时代]]》的詹姆斯·波尼沃兹克（{{lang|en|James Poniewozik}}）认为本集的剧情就是直接从“邪恶和误会的情景喜剧学校”中产生的，觉得这一集的表现让人满意，并称菲尔和克莱尔的故事桥段是“最可笑的故事线”<ref>{{cite web|last=Poniewozik |first=James |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2011/01/13/modern-family-watch-what-a-croctopus/ |title=Review of Modern Family, Our Children, Our Selves - Tuned In - TIME.com |publisher=Tunedin.blogs.time.com |date=2011-01-13 |accessdate=2013-07-24 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020222521/http://entertainment.time.com/2011/01/13/modern-family-watch-what-a-croctopus/ |archivedate=2012-10-20 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

